End Process

@Reasoning:
Classifies the name portion of a module attribute (the part after
the leading '-'). Covers Erlang's full attribute vocabulary: module
identity (module/export/import/compile/vsn), metadata
(author/copyright/doc/moduledoc), behaviour declarations
(behaviour/behavior), type system (record/type/spec/callback/opaque/
export_type/optional_callbacks), preprocessor directives
(include/include_lib/define/undef/ifdef/ifndef/else/endif), and
diagnostic directives (file/line/warning/error).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Computes substring [start, end_pos) and compares against each known
attribute via StringCore.string_equals. Each match returns the
corresponding TOKEN_* constant. Falls through to 0 to signal "not a
recognised module attribute, callers should emit TOKEN_MINUS as a
fallback".
@End Implementation
